The roof is in how the backs of prähistorischen echse, the steps, such as the vertebral column of dinosauriers and the balkone are aufgerissene fischmäuler.
This is the Casa batlló of Catalan architect Antonio gaudi in Barcelona.
Of the local inhabitants got the house with its organic forms the spitznamen "knochenhaus."
Organic forms, wild colours, the unusual use of stone, kachelsplittern and mosaiks in just erinnernde fassaden and ubiquitous soft lines, all of this is a common feature for the jugendstil Antonio gaudi.
The front of the house is playing with beautiful lines, zärtlichen paints and texturen which remind you of nature and life.
Only on closer inspection, it noted that everything is dominated by geometry, rhythm and thoughtful order.
During the night, the whole front even plastic, dramatic and the special anleuchtung exacerbates the glamour of the colours.
The same schwungvollen lines and tortuous forms control also the home of the House.
Wellenartig geformtes wood copied the fensterrahmen, geländer, zierelemente doors, and even gucklöcher and play.
The House batlló in the quarter eixample in the crowded einkaufsstraße passeig de grácia No 43 was created by the side of a house from the years 1877, the architect emilio sala cortese said.
The reconstruction, having two years and was closed 1906.
The investor, the wealthy industrial Josep batlló was originally on these are the words about the old and the construction of a completely new building, but in the end it was the idea gaudís in an unusual and also cheaper reconstruction.
